</maintainer>
<longdescription>
	Service to enable/disable, and configure, the ZSWAP
	write-back-cache frontswap hook. This (kernel) facility
	intercepts pages about to be swapped out and attempts to
	compress them, reversing the process when swapped back in. Can
	significantly improve performance on limited-memory,
	low-IO-bandwidth systems such as the RPi3.

        For more details, see e.g. https://askubuntu.com/a/472227
</longdescription>
</pkgmetadata>
